<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Article 3(2) of Council Regulation (EC) No 3072/95(4) provides for the intervention price to be subject to monthly increases. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 3072/95 (4) artikli 3 l&otilde;ikega 2 n&auml;hakse ette sekkumishinna igakuine suurendamine. </eesti>
<inglise> This mechanism seeks to take account, to some extent, of storage costs and financing charges for storing cereals in the Community and of the need to ensure that stocks are disposed of in line with market requirements. </inglise>
<eesti> Sel viisil p&uuml;&uuml;takse teataval m&auml;&auml;ral arvesse v&otilde;tta laokulusid ja rahastamiskulusid teraviljade ladustamiseks &uuml;henduses ning vajadust tagada, et varud realiseeritakse vastavalt turun&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> In accordance with the approach followed for the reform of the common organisation of the markets in connection with Agenda 2000 and in order to enable producers to organise their production over several years, the monthly increases should be fixed without any limit in time, without prejudice to any revisions that may be called for in the future. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt &uuml;hise turukorralduse reformi suunitlusele Agenda 2000 raames ja v&otilde;imaldamaks tootjatel planeerida tootmist mitme aasta ulatuses, tuleks igakuised hinnat&otilde;stmised kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata ilma ajalise piiranguta, ilma et see piiraks v&otilde;imalike muudatuste tegemist tulevikus. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular given the stability of prices and interest rates, the increases currently applicable should be maintained. </inglise>
<eesti> Arvestades eelk&otilde;ige hindade ja intressim&auml;&auml;rade stabiilsust, tuleks praegu kohaldatavad hinnat&otilde;stmised j&auml;tta samaks; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) In the context of providing support for producers of rice, Article 6 of Regulation (EC) No 3072/95 lays down a national base area for each producer Member State with the exception of France and Greece, for which two base areas are laid down. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) riisitootjate toetamise raames on m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 3072/95 artiklis 6 s&auml;testatud iga tootjaliikmesriigi kohta riiklik baask&uuml;lvipind, v&auml;lja arvatud Prantsusmaa ja Kreeka, mille puhul on s&auml;testatud kaks baask&uuml;lvipinda. </eesti>
<inglise> Greece has requested that the departments of Kavala and Aitolia and Akarnania be included in the same base area as Thessaloniki, Serres and Fthiotida, as rice constitutes a traditional crop in all of these departments. </inglise>
<eesti> Kreeka on taotlenud, et Kavala, Aitoolia ja Akarnaania maakond arvatakse Thessalon&iacute;ki, Serresi ja Fthi&oacute;tise baask&uuml;lvipinna hulka, kuna riis on tavap&auml;rane p&otilde;llukultuur k&otilde;igis nendes maakondades. </eesti>
<inglise> The total area of the base areas and the amount of the compensatory payment remain unchanged. </inglise>
<eesti> Baask&uuml;lvipindade &uuml;ldpindala ja kompenseeriva makse suurus j&auml;&auml;vad muutmata; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) With an eye to simplification and legislative clarity, the provisions of Regulation (EEC) No 3072/95 that are not relevant should be deleted at the same time. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) &otilde;igusaktide lihtsustamise ja selguse huvides tuleks j&auml;tta v&auml;lja m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3072/95 s&auml;tted, mis ei ole asjakohased; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) The measures necessary for the implementation of Regulation (EC) No 3072/95 should be adopted in accordance with Council Decision 1999/468/EC of 28 June 1999 laying down the procedures for the exercise of implementing powers conferred on the Commission(5), </inglise>
